com.customlbs.library

Class Indoors

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.customlbs.library.Indoors

  • public class Indoors
extends java.lang.Object
    The main indoo.rs public interface.

    To initialize an instance call IndoorsFactory.createInstance(Context, String, IndoorsServiceCallback) first. This instance can be retrieved with IndoorsFactory.getInstance() at any time after IndoorsServiceCallback.connected() got called.

    This interface is currently BETA and may change in future versions.

      • setLocatedBuilding

        public void setLocatedBuilding(Building building,
                      LocalizationParameters params)

        Sets the building to be located.

        After this method is called any location listeners registered will be provided with position updates. Note that if no listeners are registered at all, the service will remain in a power saving state. So don't forget to unregistered unused listeners.

        Parameters:
        building - to be located
        params - parameters used for localization, can be null, then default parameters will be used
        See Also:
        getBuilding(Building, LoadingBuildingCallback), getImportedBuildings(ImportedBuildingCallback), registerLocationListener(IndoorsLocationListener), removeLocationListener(IndoorsLocationListener)

      • enableEvaluationMode

        public void enableEvaluationMode(EvaluationParameters evaluationParameters)

        Enables evaluation mode.

        Evaluation parameters must be provided. Default parameters from default constructor are sufficient. Therefore at least one map must be known to the service, so you either must have a map in your assets/maps directory or add a directory which contains maps to the service.

        Parameters:
        evaluationParameters - must not be null
        See Also:
        EvaluationParameters, disableEvaluationMode()

      • getTileRequester

        public TileRequester getTileRequester(TileRequester.TileRequestCallback listener)

        Get an TileRequester instance which is connected to the given TileRequester.TileRequestCallback callback.

        Request tiles with returned instance. As soon as it is ready you get the corresponding call in your callback. Tiles are identified by TileKey.

        Though you can and should request all your tiles with one instance it is possible to get multiple requester.

        Parameters:
        listener -
        Returns:
        instance of tile requester
        See Also:
        TileRequester.TileRequestCallback, TileRequester.requestTile(com.customlbs.library.model.TileKey)

      • getBuilding

        public void getBuilding(Building building,
               LoadingBuildingCallback listener)

        Get a resolved building object with all member objects like floors and tiles via the LoadingBuildingCallback.

        A Building object (and its members) retrieved via this method is eligible for calls to TileRequester, setLocatedBuilding(Building, LocalizationParameters), getZones(Building, ZoneCallback), getDebugZones(Building, ZoneCallback).

        This may take some time as the building data needs to be prepared (the data is parsed from the underlying map file). Buildings passed from the getOnlineBuildings(OnlineBuildingCallback) function may take even longer as they have to be downloaded from the server.

        Parameters:
        building - the building object from getOnlineBuildings(OnlineBuildingCallback) or getImportedBuildings(ImportedBuildingCallback).
        listener - LoadingBuildingCallback to check progress
        See Also:
        setLocatedBuilding(Building, LocalizationParameters)

      • getOnlineBuildings

        public void getOnlineBuildings(OnlineBuildingCallback listener)

        Get online buildings from indoo.rs server.

        Returned building objects will not contain any floor or tile members. Only name, description, map file, lon and lat are provided. To make all members of the building object available call getBuilding(Building, LoadingBuildingCallback).

        Parameters:
        listener -
        See Also:
        getBuilding(Building, LoadingBuildingCallback)

      • getImportedBuildings

        public void getImportedBuildings(ImportedBuildingCallback listener)

        Get imported buildings from the service. These building object are not resolved so they don't contain its floor and tile members. Following members are set: name, description, map file path, lon and lat.

        Imported buildings are buildings found by the service in the assets/maps folder, or in the folders added with to the service.

        If maps from assets/maps folder are not showing up, please look for ASSET keyword in logcat. There are known problems with larger map files for android versions prior and including 2.2.

        Parameters:
        listener -
        See Also:
        addMapDirectory(File), setLocatedBuilding(Building, LocalizationParameters)

      • getRouteAToB

        public void getRouteAToB(Coordinate start,
                Coordinate end,
                RoutingCallback listener)

        Calculate a route from given coordinates. This works only for buildings that are being located and set with setLocatedBuilding(Building, LocalizationParameters).

        Expect following errors in IndoorsError.onError(IndoorsException) :
        - no route found (bad coordinates)
        - waypoints are not loaded yet (try again later, map is not fully initialized yet)

        Parameters:
        start -
        end -
        listener -

      • setLocatedCloudBuilding

        public void setLocatedCloudBuilding(long buildingId,
                           LocalizationParameters localizationParameters)

        Enables localization for given building id.

        The building is initially downloaded from the server and will be cached for consecutive calls. Server-side updates to the map will be considered if internet connection is available.

        setLocatedBuilding(Building, LocalizationParameters) is called implicitly.

        Parameters:
        buildingId -
